			<item>
				<title>Edge AI: ML inference in the browser</title>
				<link>http://localhost:1313/articles/ml_inference_browser/</link>
				<pubDate>Tue, 18 Jun 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid>http://localhost:1313/articles/ml_inference_browser/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;Recently, I stumbled across a &lt;a href=&#34;https://whisper.ggerganov.com/&#34;&gt;guy who ported&lt;/a&gt; OpenAI&amp;rsquo;s &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/openai/whisper&#34;&gt;Whisper&lt;/a&gt; model into c++, in various sizes, allowing the model to be run on-device, at impressive speed.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;!-- &lt;span class=&#34;text-gray-500 text-sm&#34;&gt;&#xA;   [(source)](https://github.com/ggerganov/whisper.cpp) &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA; --&gt;&#xA;&lt;!-- ![whisper running on iphone](/images/whisper_iphone.gif#smaller) --&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I went down a rabbit-hole, and found a whole family of popular models that had been ported to work on-device, from the browser:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://websd.mlc.ai/#text-to-image-generation-demo&#34;&gt;Stable difusion running in browser&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/jobergum/browser-ml-inference?tab=readme-ov-file&#34;&gt;Text emotion prediction in browser&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/ggerganov/llama.cpp&#34;&gt;Llama c++&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://webllm.mlc.ai/&#34;&gt;Web LLM&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://hyuto.github.io/yolov5-onnxruntime-web/&#34;&gt;YOLO in the browser&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;  &lt;img&#xA;    src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/yolo_browser.webp#smaller&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;yolo in the browser&#34;&#xA;    loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;    &#xA;  /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;figcaption&gt;yolo in the browser&lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
